Description:
JUNIOR WEB/MOBILE DEVELOPER

Company Description

We are a business based in Ikeja currently seeking a motivated and detail-oriented Junior Web/Mobile Developer to join our team. This entry-level role is ideal for someone who is passionate about web & mobile technologies, eager to learn, and ready to grow their skills in front-end and back-end development. You will work closely with senior developers and designers to build, maintain, and improve web applications that deliver excellent user experiences.

You will be required to work from our office in Ikeja Mon - Fri.

Role Description

This is a full-time on-site role for a Junior Web/Mobile Developer with both front-end and back-end skills to work from our offices in Ikeja. The post holder will be expected to be a quick learner to get up to speed working with the development team to develop both front-end and back-end functionalities of our tech products and supporting our applications.

Location: Ikeja, Lagos - Nigeria

Core Responsibilities and Duties

* Assist in developing and maintaining web and mobile applications
* Work with senior developers to implement new features and fix bugs
* Build responsive user interfaces for web and mobile
* Integrate APIs and backend services
* Participate in code reviews and team discussions
* Learn and apply best practices in software development
* Deploying websites into production
* CPanel Administration
* SSL Implementation & Website Security
* Optimizing developed features for maximum speed and scalability;
* Writing clean, readable, and testable code;
* Test, debug, and optimize applications for performance and usability
* Meet team deadlines;

Job Requirements

* Excellent Understanding web development life cycle;
* Experience with UI/UX Design;
* Excellent knowledge of REACT, HTML, CSS, Java and web development tools;
* Core working knowledge of PHP and LARAVEL;
* Database Design & Development, MYSQL/MSSQL;
* Search Engine Optimization;
* Ability to learn new concepts quickly.
* Flexible approach, self-motivated and organised;

Person Specification

* Good interpersonal skills, able to communicate in a friendly, open and constructive manner;
* Able to work on own initiative with minimal supervision;
* Ability to pay attention to details & produce work of a high standard;
* Ability to work as a team player with the team;
* Willingness and ability to learn & understand new concepts quickly;
* Passion for building software and improving skills
* Flexible approach, self-motivated and organised

Experience:

* Minimum of 12 months professional experience
* Flexible work approach, self-motivated and organised

Salary

* Range N 180,000.00 - N 250,000.00

Note

Only candidates that live in Lagos and within 30mins commuting of Ikeja would be considered

How to Apply:

Interested and qualified candidates should send their CV to recruit@gn128.com

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: ₦180,000.00 - ₦250,000.00 per month...
